thread.title: $A rises as business conditions improve

title: $A rises as business conditions improve
text:
Tue, Sep 8, 2015, 12:41 PM AEST - Australia Markets close in 3 hrs 19 mins $A rises as business conditions improve AAP â€“ 20 minutes ago Print 
The Australian dollar is higher on a quiet day of trade after a holiday in the United States. 
At 1200 AEST on Tuesday, the currency was trading at 69.63 US cents, up from 69.33 cents on Monday. 
The local currency's moves were muted overnight due to no trade in the US, and it steadily gained ground during the local morning session. 
The Australian dollar's biggest move higher came at 1130 AEST with the release of National Australia Bank's latest monthly business survey, which showed business conditions have improved to their best levels in 10 months. 
KEY MOVEMENTS: 
* 69.63 US cents, from 69.33 cents on Monday 
* 83.08 Japanese yen, from 82.72 yen 
* 62.37 euro cents, from 62.24 euro cents 
* 110.90 New Zealand cents, from 110.43 NZ cents 
* 45.56 British pence, from 45.65 pence 
Government bond yields: 
* CGS 5.5pct Jan 2018, 1.758pct, from 1.748pct on Monday 
* CGS 4.25pct April 2026, 2.729pct, from 2.731pct 
Sydney Futures Exchange prices: 
* The September 2015 10-year bond futures contract was trading at 97.310 (implying a yield of 2.690 per cent), up from 97.305 (2.695 per cent) on Monday. 
* The September 2015 three-year bond futures contract was unchanged at 98.210 (1.780 per cent). 
(*Currency closes taken at 1700 AEST previous local session, bond market closes taken at 1630 AEST previous local session) 
Source: IRESS
